# Example environment file. Names only, never real values.
#
# Real values live per environment in the Vercel project (Preview and
# Production) and, for any CI-only need, in GitHub Actions secrets. Nothing in
# this file is a secret and nothing secret is ever committed (requirement B3,
# ADR 0024). Copy to .env.local for local development; .env* is gitignored.

# Session signing secret. Set distinctly per environment in Vercel
# (Preview and Production hold different values). Consumed from Task 0.3
# onward (ADR 0008). Generate with: openssl rand -base64 32
SESSION_SECRET=

# Marks which deployment environment the agent is running in. Set per
# environment in Vercel (preview / production). Used to keep environments
# visibly distinct; not a secret.
APP_ENV=

# Optional. Only needed to route model calls through the Vercel AI Gateway
# from a non-Vercel host. On Vercel the gateway authenticates via project
# OIDC, so this is left unset there. No model calls exist yet in Phase 0.
# AI_GATEWAY_API_KEY=
